  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "My Instagram account with 8.5k followers just got hacked into. I've spent the the last hour looking up ways to hack it and trying to get it back and nothing's working. How can I get it back?",
  "response": "I'm really sorry to hear that your Instagram account has been compromised. Recovering a hacked account can be stressful, but following the right steps can help you regain control. Here's a comprehensive guide to assist you:\n\n### 1. **Don't Attempt to Hack Back**\nIt's important **not** to try hacking into your own account or using third-party services claiming to recover hacked accounts. These can lead to further security issues or scams.\n\n### 2. **Check Your Email for Instagram's Message**\nInstagram often sends an email notifying you of changes to your account (like a password reset or email change). Look for an email from Instagram to see if you can reverse any unauthorized changes.\n\n- **If you receive an email saying your email or password was changed and you didn't do it:**\n  - **Use the \"Revert this change\" link** in the email to undo the unauthorized changes.\n  \n### 3. **Use Instagram's Account Recovery Options**\nIf you can't log in, try the following steps:\n\n- **Reset Your Password:**\n  - Go to the [Instagram Login Page](https://www.instagram.com/accounts/login/).\n  - Click on **\"Forgot password?\"** or **\"Get help signing in.\"**\n  - Enter your username, email address, or phone number associated with your account.\n  - Follow the instructions to reset your password.\n\n- **Use Facebook (if Linked):**\n  - If your Instagram account is linked to Facebook, you can try logging in through Facebook.\n\n### 4. **Secure Your Email Account**\nSince your email is often linked to your Instagram account, ensure that your email hasn't been compromised:\n\n- **Change Your Email Password:**\n  - Use a strong, unique password.\n  \n- **Enable Two-Factor Authentication (2FA):**\n  - Add an extra layer of security to your email account.\n\n### 5. **Report the Hacked Account to Instagram**\nIf you\u2019re unable to regain access using the above methods, report your account as hacked:\n\n- **Use Instagram\u2019s \"Help Center\":**\n  - Visit the [Instagram Help Center](https://help.instagram.com/).\n  - Navigate to **\"Privacy and Safety Center\"** > **\"Report Something\"** > **\"Hacked Accounts.\"**\n  - Follow the prompts to submit a request for help.\n\n- **Fill Out the Hacked Account Form:**\n  - Provide required information, such as the email address, username, and any other details to verify your identity.\n\n### 6. **Check for Unauthorized Apps and Devices**\nOnce you regain access:\n\n- **Review Active Sessions:**\n  - Go to **Settings** > **Security** > **Login Activity**.\n  - Log out of any unfamiliar devices.\n\n- **Remove Suspicious Third-Party Apps:**\n  - Go to **Settings** > **Security** > **Apps and Websites**.\n  - Remove access to any apps you don't recognize or no longer use.\n\n### 7. **Enable Two-Factor Authentication (2FA)**\nAdd an extra layer of security to prevent future hacks:\n\n- Go to **Settings** > **Security** > **Two-Factor Authentication**.\n- Choose your preferred method (e.g., authentication app, SMS).\n\n### 8. **Inform Your Followers**\nLet your followers know that your account was hacked and advise them not to engage with any suspicious posts or messages sent during the hack.\n\n### 9. **Monitor Your Account and Email**\nKeep an eye on your account and related email for any unusual activity in the coming weeks.\n\n### 10. **Consider Additional Security Measures**\n- **Use a Strong, Unique Password:**\n  - Combine uppercase and lowercase letters, numbers, and symbols.\n\n- **Update Your Passwords Regularly:**\n  - Change passwords periodically to enhance security.\n\n- **Be Cautious of Phishing Attempts:**\n  - Avoid clicking on suspicious links or providing personal information to unverified sources.\n\n### 11. **Seek Professional Help if Needed**\nIf you're still unable to recover your account, consider reaching out to Instagram's support through their official channels or seeking assistance from cybersecurity professionals.\n\n---\n\n**Important Tips to Prevent Future Hacks:**\n\n- **Stay Updated:** Keep your Instagram app and device's operating system updated to the latest versions.\n- **Be Wary of Third-Party Services:** Avoid using unofficial services that promise to boost followers or engagement, as they can compromise your account.\n- **Regularly Review Security Settings:** Periodically check your account's security settings to ensure everything is in order.\n\nI hope these steps help you recover your Instagram account. If you have any more questions or need further assistance, feel free to ask!",
